# Power Manage Agent - doas configuration
# Generated by: power-manage-agent setup
# DO NOT EDIT - this file is managed by the agent binary
#
# doas(1) rule syntax has no glob / command-arg matcher equivalent to
# sudoers' "NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/apt *", so the template grants root
# without password — effectively the same capability the sudoers
# template grants cumulatively across its ~100 NOPASSWD lines. If your
# threat model requires per-binary restrictions, switch the agent to
# POWER_MANAGE_PRIVILEGE_BACKEND=sudo; doas does not support that.
#
# Activation: doas(1) only reads /etc/doas.conf by default. Ensure
# /etc/doas.conf contains:
#
#     include "/etc/doas.d/{{.User}}.conf"
#
# The agent's setup subcommand refuses to install when the include
# directive is missing so a silent "permission denied" at first
# escalation is impossible.

permit nopass {{.User}} as root
